		With any experiment, we may associate a pair $(\Omega, \mathcal{F})$, where $\Omega$ is the set of all possible outcomes or elementary events and $\mathcal{F}$ is a $\sigma$-field of subsets of $\Omega$ which contains all the events in whose occurences we may be interested in.
	\end{recap}
